The motivation here is to enable using `exp_add_of_commute` on dual numbers.


[This Zulip thread](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/116395-maths/topic/Exponentials.20in.20seminormed.20algebras/near/321981384) has some discussion about other possible norms.

nodes.body:
> The motivation here is to enable using `exp_add_of_commute` on dual numbers.

Can you please remind me of the slightly bigger picture? Where is all this heading?

There isn't really much bigger a picture here; I thought it would be nice to be able to use `NormedSpace.exp` on `DualNumber Real`, and the API for `NormedSpace.exp` is pretty unusable without a `NormedAlgebra` structure.

This PR/issue depends on:
* ~~leanprover-community/mathlib4#9491~~
* ~~leanprover-community/mathlib4#9796~~

@eric-wieser did you intend for this to still be `awaiting-author`?

I did, but as the author I had forgotten that I did that. I had intended to come back and show `inr` and `inl` are isometries; now done with `simp` lemmas. I figure there's not much point bundling them.
bors merge

Can you also update the module docstring with a brief explanation of the norm we're placing on this type and why you want it? This occurs lower in the file, but it would be nice to have it at the topic.
It would be very helpful if `gcongr` knew how to apply `norm_smul_le` and `norm_add_le` here.
If I'm not mistaken, you're pining for `grw` for which there's an open PR: #8167

There may be some argument that it is canonical. This isn't it, but related: for regular normed algebras, the ℓ¹-norm on the unitization is maximal with respect to all norms (making it into a `NormedAlgebra` satisfying `NormOneClass`) for which the embedding is an isometry. It's possible there is something similar for `TrivSqZeroExt`, but it's also possible they are not that closely related.

Should we be more careful about this and avoid abusing defeq by pulling this back through a composition of equivs? For instance see [Unitization.instUniformSpace](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Unitization.html#Unitization.instUniformSpace) and [Unitization.instBornology](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Unitization.html#Unitization.instBornology).

Also, I know that `WithLp` on products is careful to replace the topology with the product topology, but can you add an `example` verifying this for `TrivSqZeroExt`?

I think the defeq abuse is fine here; it's not exposed in any lemma statements, so is an implementation detail.

I would be more open to using the "right" way of doing things if it actually kept the nice defeqs, but without some of the constructions in #8961 I think that's currently not the case (which is why you have to prove a bunch of things to copy the structure, while I don't).

```suggestion
    rw [mul_comm, MulOpposite.norm_op]
    exact le_add_of_nonneg_right <| by positivity
```

You don't need the `𝕜` variables here
```suggestion
variable [NormedCommRing R] [NormedAddCommGroup M]
variable [Module R M] [Module Rᵐᵒᵖ M] [IsCentralScalar R M]
variable [BoundedSMul R M]
```
This is subject to the same comment above. Should we avoid abuse of defeq here and pull back the uniform structure explicitly?
